	.about.js-menu-watch#about
		.about-in
			h2.s-title.s-title_short About us
			.about-text
				p Though there are a wide variety of competitions available for university students – we feel that it is especially crucial for those with entrepreneurial spirit to be able to express their ideas and develop their talents in this field. 
				p Thus, the Global Young Entrepreneurs Competition (GYEC) was founded on the premise of encouraging young entrepreneurship across the globe.
		
	.requir.js-menu-watch#requir
		.requir-in
			.requir-inin
				.requir-ininin
					h2.s-title Entry Requirements
					.requir-content
						.requir-el Competitors will be required to submit an entrepreneurial <br>‘pitch’ of not more than 2,000 words.
						.requir-el The purpose of this ‘pitch’ is to be able to sell the judging panel a sound entrepreneurial business model. Students should imagine that they are attempting to convince a board of venture capitalists to fund their start-up project to pursue in real life.
						.requir-el As such, contestants should articulate their ideas clearly, and also demonstrate a degree of financial planning. For example, basic calculations of initial capital requirements or average running costs would be encouraged.
						.requir-el Importantly, these pitches can be for either <br>for-profit or not-for-profit ideas. 

